{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"87cd2e00-0a09-4869-bd9f-9c61f4ce5c04","content":"Here's the mapping from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP):\n\n| VSTest flag | MTP equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/[Tag=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**New command** (passing MTP args after `--`):\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/[Tag=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Required NuGet packages** in your test project:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- Enable MTP in your project: `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>`\n- MTP uses **tree-node filter syntax** (`/[Tag=X]`) instead of VSTest's `--filter`. If your tests use `[TestCategory(\"Integration\")]`, the MTP equivalent property name is `Tag`.\n- If you prefer to keep VSTest filter syntax, some frameworks (e.g., MSTest) offer a compatibility bridge — check your test framework docs.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f3c72489-63e4-4926-948c-49815902db5d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences between VSTest and MTP:\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` \n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with coverage settings\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\n\n- `--treenode-filter` is the native MTP filter syntax when running the test executable directly\n\nI need to clarify whether they're using `dotnet test` as a wrapper or running the MTP executable directly, since the flag syntax differs between the two approaches. I need to clarify the exact syntax for MTP integration with `dotnet test` — in .NET 8 you still default to VSTest, but you can enable MTP support through project configuration, and in .NET 9+ there's native integration with different flag handling. I'm working through the specific NuGet packages needed for MTP extensions—TrxReport, CodeCoverage, CrashDump, and HangDump—along with their corresponding command-line flags like `--filter`, `--report-trx`, `--coverage`, and timeout options that can be passed through `dotnet test` after the `--` separator.","outputTokens":1566,"requestId":"0430:1C7D40:1E72FB3:2245555:69E81A4D"},"id":"d8ae18c7-814a-4457-886c-a7553afc8b4e","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:46:32.906Z","parentId":"bad1882a-6ea9-4a1e-9e5e-8b51fa42b191"}
